            . I am in the employ of Ann and Eliza Garton - they are <rs id="t18250915-323-viclabel1744" type="occupation">hosiers</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-323-victim1621 t18250915-323-viclabel1744"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-323-victim1622 t18250915-323-viclabel1744"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18250915-323-crimeloc1745">Cheapside</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-323-crimeloc1745" type="placeName" value="Cheapside"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-323-crimeloc1745" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-323-off1742 t18250915-323-crimeloc1745"></join>; this handkerchief is their property. On the 10th of August, it laid on the right hand counter, where we expose goods for sale. I did not miss it, till the officer brought in the prisoner about twelve o'clock.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-323-person1624">
                  DANIEL 
                  FORRESTER
               <interp inst="t18250915-323-person1624" type="surname" value="FORRESTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-323-person1624" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-323-person1624" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On Wednesday, the 10th of August, I was going past the shop with a prisoner, and saw this lad come from the door with something yellow under his jacket; I went into the shop and said to the young man, "Have you sold a yellow handkerchief;" he said, No; I said, "If you will take care of my prisoner, I will go and see if I can get it;" I went to Bow-lane, and took the prisoner with this handkerchief under his coat.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was coming from Mitcham, and saw the handkerchief lying on the ground; I picked it up - the constable came and took me.</p>
               <p>
